---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Math Explorations — Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Interactive visualizations exploring chaos theory, prime patterns, random walks, and wave mathematics."
>
  <section class="hero section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Math Explorations</h1>
      <p class="hero-text">I keep running into math concepts that make way more sense when you can see them. So I started building these — each one is something I wanted to understand better. Drag the sliders, mess with the parameters, and watch what happens.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="demos section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="demo-grid">
        <a href="/math-explorations/chaos" class="demo-card" data-accent="blue">
          <div class="card-border"></div>
          <h3>Chaos Theory</h3>
          <p>One equation, zero randomness, and somehow it produces total chaos</p>
          <span class="demo-link">Explore Demo →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/math-explorations/primes" class="demo-card" data-accent="orange">
          <div class="card-border"></div>
          <h3>Prime Spirals</h3>
          <p>Primes are supposed to be random. So why do they line up in diagonals?</p>
          <span class="demo-link">Explore Demo →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/math-explorations/walks" class="demo-card" data-accent="green">
          <div class="card-border"></div>
          <h3>Random Walks</h3>
          <p>Flip a coin 1000 times. The pattern that shows up shouldn't exist, but it does</p>
          <span class="demo-link">Explore Demo →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/math-explorations/fourier" class="demo-card" data-accent="purple">
          <div class="card-border"></div>
          <h3>Fourier Series</h3>
          <p>Any wave — no matter how jagged — is just sine waves stacked up</p>
          <span class="demo-link">Explore Demo →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why I Built These</h2>
      <p>I kept hitting concepts in math that I could solve on paper but didn't really <em>get</em>. Building something where I can see the math moving helped it click in a way textbooks never did. Each demo started with a question I couldn't stop thinking about.</p>
      <p class="honest-note">Honest note: I used AI tools to help with the coding — I'm not a programmer. But the math design — what to visualize, what parameters matter, what's actually interesting to explore — that part is mine. The AI can't do that because it doesn't know what I'm trying to understand.</p>
      <a href="/" class="button">← Back to Home</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--light-gray) 0%, var(--white) 100%);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .hero-text {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  .demos {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }

  .demo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .demo-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .demo-card {
    position: relative;
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
    overflow: hidden;
    min-height: 200px;
  }

  .demo-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .card-border {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 4px;
  }

  .demo-card[data-accent="blue"] .card-border {
    background-color: var(--blue);
  }

  .demo-card[data-accent="orange"] .card-border {
    background-color: var(--orange);
  }

  .demo-card[data-accent="green"] .card-border {
    background-color: #27AE60;
  }

  .demo-card[data-accent="purple"] .card-border {
    background-color: #9B59B6;
  }

  .demo-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  .demo-card p {
    flex: 1;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .demo-link {
    color: var(--blue);
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .demo-card:hover .demo-link {
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  .about {
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about p {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-md);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .honest-note {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #555;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero-text {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .about p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
